#Text=helictite - a speleothem, which at one or more stages of its growth changes its axis from the vertical to give a curving or angular form.
#Text=hydrology - the scientific study of the nature, distribution and behaviour of water.
#Text=ice cave - a cave with perennial ice in it.
#Text=inflow cave - a cave into which a stream enters or is known to have entered formerly but which cannot be followed downstream to the surface.
#Text=karren - the minor forms of karst as a result of solution of rock on the surface or underground.
#Text=karst - tereain with special landforms and drainage characteristics on account of greater solubility of certain rocks in natural waters than is common.
#Text=karst window - a dosed depression, not a polje, which has a stream flowing across its bottom.
#Text=keyhole - a small passage or opening in a cave, which is round above and narrow below.
#Text=lava-cave - a cave in a lava flow; usually a tube or tunnel formed by flow of liquid lava through a solidified mass, or by roofing of an open channel of flowing lava.
#Text=limestone - a sedimentary rock consisting mainly of calcium carbonate cac03•
#Text=live cave - a cave containing a stream or active speleothems.marble limestone recrystallized and hardened by pressure and heat.
#Text=meander niche - a hemispherically roofed part of a cave formed by a stream meandering and cutting down at the same time.
#Text=moonmilk - a soft, white plastic speleothem consisting of calcite, hydrocalcite, hydromagnesite or huntite.
#Text=natural arch - an arch of rock formed by weathering.
#Text=natural bridge - a bridge of rock spanning a ravine or valley and formed by erosive agents.
